cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.CY, cs.LG 

This paper deals with the use of machine learning classifiers to identify depressive symptoms from Twitter data, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves feature selection and optimization, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with mental health monitoring, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
